plan_validation[1]{text}:
  "Orchestrator independent verification 2026-05-23 (rebuilt dist from current source): reviewed full diff for code quality (pure logic in core/schema/item-types-file.ts, IO/governance in cli/commands/schema.ts, hint wired into create.ts:1581+update.ts:1734 via buildInvalidTypeError, all wiring sites present: index/register-mutation/mcp-server/sdk-cli-contracts/contracts/completion). Independent temp-dir dogfood = 20/20 effective: builtin create still works; invalid-type error now contains 'pm schema add-type' + 'schema/types.json' + keeps Allowed list; schema add-type human+json; create custom type + via alias works; idempotent upsert (single def); built-in collision rejected; bare/unknown subcommand rejected; contracts expose --default-status; list/get/update/search/validate/health all green. Shell completions confirmed to include schema across bash+zsh+fish (with guide-shell package). Full release gate running."
plan_decisions[1]{ts,author,decision}:
  "2026-05-23T11:36:37.862Z",claude-code-agent,"New top-level `pm schema` mutation command family, starting with `schema add-type`, rather than overloading `pm config`."
plan_discoveries[1]{ts,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T11:51:39.021Z",claude-code-agent,"schema add-type stores the supplied name verbatim as the canonical name on upsert (case-insensitive match), so re-running with a different case rewrites the stored case; create/update still resolve any case + aliases via registry.alias_to_type, so this is harmless. completion.ts ALL_COMMANDS derives from PM_CORE_COMMAND_NAMES (auto), but the fish __pm_no_subcommand list and zsh _pm_commands description list are hand-maintained and were updated explicitly."
